    Class Description
    AccessibleTile
    Represents ta tile that the player can walk on.
    Baboon
    An AI that plays based on purely random inputs.
    BoardRenderer
    A renderer to visually display the state of the game board.
    Capuchin
    An AI that tries to play the game intelligently.
    CapuchinTest
    Testing suite for the Capuchin model AI, which tries to play the game properly.
    Chap
    Represents Chap who is the hero of the game.
    Colour
    Possible colours for keys and doors.
    DecayTile
    Represents a tile that decays each time Chap walks out of it, becomes a WallTile when Chap walks over it enough times.
    Direction
    Possible directions of movement.
    DoorTile
    Represents a tile that is a locked door that the player cannot go through
    Entity
    Represents an object that is a character that moves around the map.
    ExitLockTile
    Represents the locked exit tile in the level,is only unlocked when Chap moves to the door while holding a key with the same colour.
    ExitTile
    Represents the exit tile in the level, when the player enters this tile the level is finished.
    FreeTile
    Represents an empty tile in the level.
    Gorilla
    An AI that tries to push through walls where possible.
    GorillaTest
    Testing suite for the Gorilla model AI, which tries to push through doors and walls.
    GUI
    Builds the Graphic User Interface.
    Icon
    Represents an object in the maze that will be drawn by the renderer.
    InaccessibleTile
    Represents ta tile that the player can walk on
    InfoTile
    Represents a tile that displays information when the player walks onto it.
    InventoryRenderer
    A renderer to visually display the player's inventory.
    KeyTile
    Represents the tile in the game that contains a key.
    Lemur
    An AI that picks up keys but ignores treasures, while trying to reach the exit.
    LemurTest
    Testing suite for the Lemur model AI, which avoids treasures and tries to move through the exit lock.
    Levels
    A class for loading levels from the json files.
    LevelsTest  
    Main
    Run the game.
    Maze
    Represents the map used in the game for each level.
    MonkeyAI
    Abstract class representing the contractual requirements of MonkeyAI players.
    Moves
    Possible moves that Chap can do.
    NPC
    Represents a nonChap entity in the level.
    Persistence
    A class for the saving and loading of the game state for the game.
    Record
    Class to create a record and write out the players movements.
    Replay
    Class to create a replay of the movements made by the player for the previous level.
    SoundRenderer
    A class to handle playing game sounds.
    Tile
    Represents a tile in the board.
    TreasureTile
    Represents the tile in the game that contains a treasure
    WallTile
    Represents the wall tile in the level.
